-IMM--AN.definition: an adjectival affix meaning: to be truly in the state or condition described by the stem.
-IMM--AN.eng_example: You are truly a man and yet you are cowardly.

-IN-.definition: pt. of -EN. a nominalizing affix identical to the pt. form of -EN; the meaning is: one that has undergone the action or process expressed by the verb stem. an adverbial affix meaning: every, each.
-IN-.eng_example: Every year his wife gives birth to a child. (+ R1), an adjective affix meaning: to tend to be what the stem describes.
-IN-.ilok_example: Tinawen nga aganak diay baket na.

-INN-.definition: a verbal affix indicating reciprocity in the performance of the action expressed by the (verbal) stem. + -AN, 1. with a verbal stem, a var. of -INN-. 2. with an adjectival stem, it indicates competition or rivalry in showing the quality or attribute expressed by the stem.

I.definition: to (be able to) overtake or reach.
I.eng_example: He was the one who overtook me. had a nightmare last night. can see a hand dangling out of that window.

I.definition: to hang  dangle downwards (out of an opening).
I.eng_example: Don’t dangle that child (out of the window). ’ll vote tomrow.
I.ilok_example: Saan mo nga bittayonen dayta ubing.

I.eng_example: Vote f me, huh? went. 4. sluggish, slow  dull from loss of vitality.

I.definition: to ask for the hand of a girl in marriage for someone, to propose marriage to a girl for someone.
I.eng_example: They will go ask for the hand of Mary in marriage (for someone).

I.definition: 1. to take to, cause to reach.
I.eng_example: Will you please take my book to our house. 2. to report to someone, cause to reach someone.
I.ilok_example: Idanon mo man daytoy librok idiay balay mi.

I-.definition: [with pl. goal] to set down on, put or place down on or in.
to set, put or place down the load of.
I-.eng_example: Please put down my load. (+ R2) before a vowel.

I-.definition: to cause (a parade, procession, etc.) to pass by or through.
I-.eng_example: Have the parade pass by our house.
I-.ilok_example: Ilabas mo diay parada ditoy balay mi.

I-.conjugation: / to explain, elucidate, elaborate on; to make clear. /

I-.definition: to refuse (to move), to refuse to make a motion (to do something).
I-.eng_example: Why do you refuse to move?
I-.ilok_example: Apay nga ipakpakutibeg mo ti aggunay?
I-.conjugation: / to throw into the eyes of. /

I-.eng_example: Don’t make your wound visible to me.
I-.ilok_example: Saan mo nga iparang kaniak dayta sugat mo.
I-.conjugation: / to eat (an article of food) with (another). /
/ to bribe with, to use to bribe (someone). /

I-.definition: to cause to fall to the ground.
to give as help, aid, or assistance.
to keep for someone expected to come or arrive. (+ R2) before a vowel.

IBAGAM.definition: TA UMAY, tell him to come.

IBAR-IBAR.definition: to totter, stagger, sway, wobble as in walking.

IBBAT.definition: to stop holding onto something with the hand or hands.
to release one’s hold of, to let go, fall, drop, etc. by releasing one’s hold of.

IBBUNG.definition: to become spoiled as an egg or as like an egg.
IBBUNG.eng_example: All the eggs of their hen became spoiled.
IBBUNG.ilok_example: Nagibbung amin nga itlog ti manok da.

IBLENG.definition: to have diarrhea, to have loose bowel movement.

IBTUR.definition: to tolerate, endure, bear, suffer, withstand.

IBUS.definition: to consume completely, to dispose of completely, to finish; to eat all.
to be completely consumed or disposed of; to be completely eaten.

IDA.definition: they, them (in passive sentences): the enclitic nominative of ISUDA.

IDDA.definition: to cause to lie down, be prostrate; to lay down in horizontal position, to lay prostrate.

IDDEP.ilok_example: Sino ti nangiddep ti silaw ko?

IDI.definition: to give up, leave off; to stop from doing.
in the distant or remote past, formerly, then.
IDI.eng_example: My father then was a policeman.

IDI.definition: last, the past (night, morning, etc.): forms prepositional phrases expressing past time.

IDI.eng_example: I was sleeping when you came. form of DAYDI postposed to a noun expressing emphasis.

IDIAY.definition: to, in, at, from, toward, away from.
variations: DIAY. form of DAYDIAY postposed to a noun expressing emphasis

IDNA.definition: to be quiet, calm, still, tranquil.
IDNA.eng_example: I cannot keep calm on account of my worry.
IDNA.ilok_example: Diak nga makaidna ti danag ko.

IDOS.definition: to spoon; to take up with or as with a spoon.
IDOS.eng_example: Take some of the sidedish with a spoon.

IGAD.definition: to grate (coconut meat or something else).

IGGEM.definition: to hold, grasp or clutch (someone or something).

IGID.definition: to go to the edge, brink or side (of).

IGLESIA.definition: FILIPINA INDEPENDIENTE, the Philippine Independent Church, also known as the Aglipayan Church.
IGLESIA.cross_reference: NI KRISTO (CHURCH OF CHRIST), 1. a church founded in the Philippines. 2. (often shortened to IGLESIA) a member of this church

IGOROT.definition: a general name for the natives of the Mountain Province.

IGUP.definition: to sip, suck; to draw liquid into the mouth by sucking and
by letting the liquid flow into it.

IIL.definition: to whimper or whine importunately or annoyingly.

IIT.definition: midrib of coconut or buri leaf.

IKA-.definition: a verbalizing affix occurring with adjective roots which expresses the meaning: in the manner or with the characteristic indicated by the root.

IKAB.definition: to eat something surreptitiously or secretly.

IKAB.eng_example: He ate surreptitiously all the sidedish which I hid.
IKAB.ilok_example: Inikab na amin nga sida nga indulin ko.

IKAMEN.definition: mat made of the leaves of the buri palm or any similar material.

IKDAL.definition: fishbone, or something similar to it, caught in the alimentary canal in the region of the throat.
to have a fishbone or something similar caught in the alimentary canal in the region of the throat.

IKET.definition: any net used for catching fish, shrimps, etc.

IKING.definition: edge of a board, book, etc.

IKK-.definition: to be given, granted, bestowed, conferred (something).
variations: of ITDAN (?). Ikkan nak man ti kanek. Please give me something to eat

IKKAT.eng_example: He will remove the door of their house.
IKKAT.ilok_example: Ikkaten na diay ridaw ti balay da.

IKKAT.definition: to resign from (a position, a job, etc.).
to be removed from (a position. a job, etc.).

IKUB.ilok_example: Adda da iti ikub ti estudio.

IKUT.definition: to hold or keep in one’s possession; to have, possess.
IKUT.eng_example: It is bad to hold in one’s possession what one does not own.
IKUT.ilok_example: Dakes nga ikutan ti saan mo nga kukua.

ILAD.definition: 1. to lie and rub the body on the floor lazily.
ILAD.eng_example: All he did was to lie and rub his body on the floor lazily. 2. to lie prostrate due to pain, exhaustion, etc.

ILAD.definition: to lie and rub the body on the floor lazily with, to be wearing (it) when lying and rubbing the body on the floor lazily.
ILAD.eng_example: Don’t lie and rub your body lazily on the floor with your new clothes.
ILAD.ilok_example: Saan mo nga iyilad dayta baro nga badom.

ILALA.definition: to value, treasure; to cherish, esteem; to take care of dearly; to hold and keep with affection; to appreciate.
ILALA.eng_example: You treasure what I gave you.

ILALA.definition: alas!, what a pity!, it’s a pity!

ILANG-ILANG.definition: 1. a tree that bears fragrant flowers. 2. a flower of this tree.

ILIW.definition: to be homesick (for someone or something), to be nostalgic, to be lonesome for.

ILO.definition: to wipe the anus after defecating.
to wipe the anus (of someone) after defecating.

ILOKANO.definition: 1. one of the Philippine languages spoken principally in Northern Luzon. 2. a speaker, especially a native speaker, of this language.

synonyms: MASAHE 2. to set (broken bones) by massaging. 3. to deliver a baby by massaging and pushing

IM-.definition: var, of IN-occurring before P or B.

IM-IMA.definition: to thwart, frustrate, bring to naught, cause to fail.
to be thwarted, frustrated, brought to naught, caused to fail.

IMA.definition: 1. arm. 2. hand. 3. something like or corresponding to an arm. see IM-IMA.

IMAS.eng_example: He enjoys staying in the forest.

IMATANG.eng_example: He won’t remove his sight from Mary.
IMATANG.ilok_example: Dina isina ti imatang na ken ni Maria.

IMATANG.definition: to pay attention to, watch, see, witness, observe.
IMATANG.eng_example: Pay attention to the one speaking.

IMATON.definition: to watch, see; to attend, e.g. a show.

IMBAG.definition: good: 1. kind. 2. skillful, competent, efficient. 3. pleasing, gratifying, enjoyable. 4. well, no longer sick. 5. proper, becoming, right.

IMPUSUAN.eng_example: He gave him his wholehearted support.
IMPUSUAN.ilok_example: Inted na kanyana ti naimpusuan nga tulong na.

IN-INAYAD.definition: to move or do something slowly, gently and carefully.
to do slowly, gently and carefully.
IN-INAYAD.eng_example: Carry my suitcase slowly, gently and carefully for there is something breakable inside it.
IN-INAYAD.ilok_example: In-inayaden yo nga bagkaten dayta maletak ta adda mabuong.

IN-INUT.definition: 1. to do little by little, every now and then, a little at a time, 2. to use or consume economically, a little at a time, little by little.
IN-INUT.eng_example: Eat that sidedish economically for there is no more.
IN-INUT.ilok_example: In-inuten yo dayta sida ta awanen.

INA.definition: an exclamation expressing mild displeasure or impatience; usually preceded by AY.
INA.ilok_example: Ay ina, nagbuntog kan! Oh my, you are so slow! ÍNA,

INA.definition: a girl, one’s young daughter: used affectionately. ÍNA,
a title of respect for an older woman.

INAKBAY.definition: to diffuse, spread, e.g. odors, smoke, etc.
INAKBAY.eng_example: The smell of the sidedish is spreading here.
INAKBAY.ilok_example: Aginakbay ti angot ti sida ditoy.

INALADAN.definition: fenced portion of a yard or lot.

INANA.definition: to rest, to cease from action or motion.
INANA.eng_example: Let’s rest for I am already tired.

INANAK.definition: child, offspring, son, daughter. see under ANAK.

INANAMA.definition: to hope, trust, rely on, have confidence in.

INANG.definition: syn. of INA: usually used as a term of address.

INAUDI.definition: 1. a younger brother or sister. 2. youngest child.

INAUNA.definition: 1. elder brother or sister. 2. eldest child; first-born child.

INAW.definition: to be at the early period of conception characterized by vomiting and
capricious desire to eat certain foods; to conceive, become pregnant.

INDAYON.definition: 1. to use a swing or cradle for recreation. 2. to swing, sway.
to put in a cradle or hammock, to rock in a cradle or hammock.

INDENG.definition: to listen to, heed; to hearken.

INDIAK.definition: I don’t want to, I refuse (to do it).

ING-.definition: var. of IN-occurring before K or G.

INGAS.definition: one similar or resembling (another one) in physical features.
INGAS.eng_example: He resembles his father in physical features.

INGAS.definition: to be similar, to resemble each other in physical features.

INGEL.definition: brave, courageous, valiant, daring, bold, heroic.
strong: said of liquors, tobacco, etc.

INGEP.eng_example: What I am imagining is roast pig.

INGGA.definition: until, till, up to (a place, time).
variations: INGGANA, AGINGGA, AGINGGANA TI, until, till the time that, up to the time that
INGGANA TI, AGINGGA TI, AGINGGANA TI, INGGAT, INGGANAT, AGINGGAT, AGINGGANAT

INGGET.eng_example: The young lady is very very beautiful.

INGUNGOT.definition: to love dearly, to be very fond of.

INIIN.definition: to shake or be unstable due to the uneven distribution of its weight or contents: said of containers.
INIIN.eng_example: Compress the contents of that box so that it won’t shake.
INIIN.ilok_example: Pekpekem dayta kahon tapno saan nga aginiin.

INIRUBAN.definition: the rice resulting from such action.

INIT.definition: to shine, to have the sun shining.
INIT.eng_example: Do you think the sun will shine tomorrow?

INIT.definition: to be exposed to the sun, to be hit or burned by the sun.
INIT.eng_example: Let’s go under the tree so that we will not be hit by the sun.
INIT.ilok_example: Intayo idiay sirok ti kayo tapno saan tayo nga mainitan.

INNAW.definition: to wash plates, bowls, and other things used in eating a meal.
to wash (things used in eating a meal).

INNUROG.definition: to spin smoothly: said of tops and similar objects.

INPAKSET.definition: burned or scorched rice or meat.

INSIK.definition: 1. the Chinese language. 2. a Chinese person. 3. figuratively: a cunning person especially in business, a cheater especially in business.

INTAR.definition: to fall in line, stand in a line or row.
to fall in line with others, stand in a line with others.
to place in a line or row, to file, Intaren na dagidiay pinggan ditoy.
INTAR.ilok_example: He will place the plates in a row here.

INTAR.definition: to be standing in a line, to be placed in a row.
INTAR.eng_example: There are many cars placed in a row within the premises of the house.
INTAR.ilok_example: Adu ti naintar nga lugan iti arubayan ti balay.

INTEK.eng_example: Don’t stay where you are going.
INTEK.ilok_example: Saan ka nga agintek idiay papanam.

INTERES.definition: interest: readiness to be concerned with or moved by an object or class of object.
INTERES.eng_example: I have no interest in what you are doing.
INTERES.ilok_example: Awan ti interes ko dita ar-aramidem.

INTERES.definition: n, a charge for borrowed money.

INTERMEDIA.definition: the intermediate stage in the elementary school; the fifth and sixth grades and also seventh grade (if any) in the elementary school.

variations: INTON, TONO. KET NO, lest. NGARUD NO, if. INTONO

INTON.eng_example: BIGAT TI MALEM or INTON MALEM NO BIGAT, tomorrow afternoon. var. of 1,2INTONO.
INTON.ilok_example: BIGAT TI AGSAPA or INTON AGSAPA NO BIGAT, tomorrow morning.

INTONANO.definition: INTON-ANO, inter. when?, at what time? (in the future).

INTONO.eng_example: When I come here do you think you will be here?
INTONO.ilok_example: Intono umayak ditoy, adda ka ngata?

INTONO.eng_example: Don’t be noisy lest he gets angry.
INTONO.ilok_example: Saan ka nga natagari intono agunget.

synonyms: SALUDSUD Intuodem no ania ti kayat na. Ask what he wants

INUDO.definition: to warm oneself in front of a fire or any other hot object.

INUMEN.eng_example: Do you have something to drink?

IPA-.origin: 1. I- + PA- (causative): the goal of the noncausative verb is placed in focus or subject position. 2. I-+ PA (to go): the goal of the verb (PA) is placed in focus or subject position. 3. I-+

IPIL.definition: a leguminous tree which yields valuable timber.

IPIT.definition: 1, pincers: a grasping claw, as of a crab or lobster; chela. 2. var. of SIPIT.
to pinch: to squeeze between two surfaces, two edges, etc.

IPUS.definition: to put a tail on or to.

IRAY.definition: to incline, lean, slant, Nagiray diay balay da kalpasan ti bagyo.
IRAY.ilok_example: Their house inclined after the typhoon.

IRAY.definition: to cause to incline, lean, slant.
IRAY.eng_example: You cause that wall to incline.

IRI.definition: to produce a long shrill cry.

IRIG.definition: to incline, bend down on one side.
to cause to incline, bend down on one side.

IRIK.definition: separate rice grains from the harvested stalks especially with the feet.
to separate the grains of (harvested rice), to thresh rice grains.

IRIK-IRIK.definition: to step on or trample someone moving the feet as when separating rice grains from the stalks.

IRTENG.definition: tightly drawn, taut, not loose, stretched tightly.

IRUB.definition: to roast young or immature rice grains which are pounded afterwards in order to flatten the grains and separate the husks.

IRUT.eng_example: Tighten the tie of your shoes.
IRUT.ilok_example: Irutem dayta tali ti sapatos mo.

IS-ISU.definition: he or she only, he or she alone.

ISBO.definition: to urinate or wet on (someone or something).
ISBO.eng_example: Your dog wetted on my plant.

ISEK.definition: to fit, to be correctly adjusted to or shaped for.
ISEK.ilok_example: Saan nga umsek dayta sapatos mo kanyak.

ISEK.definition: to make fit in or on, to put on (shoes).

ISEM.definition: always smiling, full of smiles; cheerful.
ISEM.eng_example: Bert is always smiling no matter how tired he is.
ISEM.ilok_example: Naisem ni Berto uray kasano ti bannog na.

ISIP.definition: to think of, consider, ponder, reflect upon (what to do).

ISO.definition: to rub the dirt off one’s body, to scrub oneself.
to rub the dirt off (someone’s) body, to scrub.

ISPAL.definition: to obstruct the throat of, to choke.
to have the throat obstructed by food, to be choked by food.

ISPAL.ilok_example: Ispalen na kami ti nakaro nga sakit.

ISU.definition: he, she; him, her: the person previously mentioned.
ISU.ilok_example: ISU is the full nominative case form, ISU or zero (nothing) the enclitic nominative, KUKUANA the full possessive, NA the enclitic possessive and the agent, and KANYANA or KENKUANA the oblique.

ISU.eng_example: If it is the will of God, we can’t do anything.
ISU.ilok_example: No isu ti kayat ti dios, awan ti maaramid tayo.

ISU.definition: to be enough or sufficient, to fit.
an emphatic particle; it is followed by NGA before a clause.
ISU.eng_example: It is that from which problems come.
ISU.ilok_example: Isu dayta ti paggapoan ti kirokiro ita.

ISUDA.definition: they; them: the persons previously mentioned. is the full nominative case form, DA or IDA the enclitic nominative, KUKUADA the full possessive, DA the enclitic possessive and the agent, and KANYADA or KENKUADA the oblique.

IT.definition: a sound that someone makes to tell someone else that he is hiding and that the other should look for him. If the person hiding comes out suddenly and wishes to startle the other, he cries BA

IT-IT.definition: to produce a thin high-pitched sound like the cry of snakes, rats, etc.

ITA.definition: var. of 1,2ITATTA. form of DAYTA postposed to a noun expressing emphasis.
ITA.eng_example: That child there is the one who is noisy.

ITATTA.definition: now, at the present time, at this moment.
this (morning, night, etc.): forms prepositional phrases expressing present time.

ITATTAY.definition: in the immediate past, in the near past, a moment ago.
ITATTAY.eng_example: Your child was here a moment ago.
ITATTAY.ilok_example: Adda itattay diay anak mo ditoy.

ITATTAY.definition: last, the immediate or near past (morning, night, etc.): forms prepositional phrases expressing immediate or near past time.
when (in the immediate or near past).

ITAY.definition: var. of 1,2,3ITATTAY. form of DAYTAY postposed to a noun expressing emphasis.

ITED.definition: to give, grant (something) to; to confer, bestow (something) on.
ITED.eng_example: He does not want to give money to his wife.
ITED.ilok_example: Saan na kayat ti mangted ti kuarta idiay baket na.

ITI.definition: DAMO NA, at first, in the beginning. cm. indefinite goal marker.
as for, concerning (a person, place or thing).
ITI.eng_example: As for a man, he is stronger than a woman.
ITI.ilok_example: Iti lalaki, napigpigsa ngem ti babai.

ITI.definition: because of, on account of, due to, in.
ITI.eng_example: In his irritation, he wanted to twist my neck.
ITI.ilok_example: Iti rurod na, kayat na nga tiritiren ti tengnged ko.

ITNEG.definition: a name applied to the natives of the province of Abra.

ITOY.definition: form of DAYTOY postposed to a noun expressing emphasis.

ITTA.definition: in milled rice, unhusked grains mixed with the husked ones.
in milled rice, to remove remaining unhusked grains from the husked ones.
to remove unhusked grains from (milled rice).

ITTIP.definition: crust of rice found at the bottom of the pot; it is usually harder and slightly burned.

ITUM.definition: to close (mouth, etc.)-Itumem ta ngiwat mo.

IY-.definition: var. of 1,2I- occurring before a vowel.

IYAAY.definition: nominalized form of AY: the coming or arrival (of).

IYOT.definition: to copulate with, to engage in sexual intercourse with.
to copulate or engage in sexual intercourse with each other.
